ing%20it%20easy%20to%20leapfrog%20off%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20only%20takes%20a%20puff%20of%20fuel%20to%20leave%20the%20mini-moon%20and%20head%20back%20towards%20Earth%2C%26quot%3B%20Richard%20Binzel%2C%20a%20planetary%20scientist%20at%20MIT%2C%20previously%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2Fspace%2Fspace-exploration%2Fundiscovered-minimoons-may-orbit-earth-could-they-help-us-become-an-interplanetary-species%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELive%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bf8bc193-7a0a-4a09-9d9c-2c6ac7e8d411%5C%22%3EMini-moon%20missions%20at%20the%20ready%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20problem%20with%20mini-moons%20is%20that%20scientists%20sometimes%20don't%20see%20them%20coming%20until%20a%20few%20weeks%20before%20they're%20captured%20in%20our%20planet's%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsteroid%202024%20PT5%2C%20for%20example%2C%20was%20first%20identified%20as%20a%20mini-moon%20in%20early%20September%20and%20will%20only%20be%20in%20Earth's%20orbit%20for%20about%2057%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20tight%20timeline%20for%20preparing%20and%20launching%20a%20mining%20mission.%20For%20any%20asteroid%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20need%20to%20learn%20enough%20about%20it%20to%20know%20whether%20it's%20worth%20sending%20a%20rocket%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Kareta%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsteroid-mining%20companies%20can%20work%20around%20that%20by%20having%20mining%20spacecraft%20ready%20in%20Earth's%20orbit%2C%20waiting%20for%20the%20right%20space%20rock%20to%20zoom%20by%2C%20Marcos%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEither%20if%20you%20are%20thinking%20about%20collecting%20mineral%20samples%20for%20research%20or%20starting%20a%20space%20mining%20venture%2C%20mini-moons%20are%20your%20best%20bet%20to%20get%20your%20business%20off%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearth-second-moon-represents-