20in%20college.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20said%20he%20has%20been%20working%20hard%20to%20represent%20others%20in%20his%20community%20in%20red%20states.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EJavier%20R.%20Quiroz%20Castro%20is%20a%20beneficiary%20of%20DACA%2C%20or%20Deferred%20Action%20for%20Childhood%20Arrivals%2C%20a%20policy%20introduced%20by%20the%20Obama%20administration%20in%202012%20that%20grants%20relief%20from%20deportation%20to%20undocumented%20immigrants%20brought%20to%20the%20country%20as%20children.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Quiroz%2C%2032%2C%20from%20near%20Houston%2C%20Texas%2C%20about%20pursuing%20a%20nursing%20career%20in%20the%20US.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20parents%20come%20from%20a%20small%2C%20poor%20town%20in%20Mexico.%20They%20didn't%20see%20a%20future%20for%20me%20there%20and%20knew%20other%20people%20who%20moved%20to%20the%20US%20in%20search%20of%20a%20better%20life%2C%20so%20they%20decided%20to%20do%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-and-uk-life-biggest-differences-after-moving-home-space-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecame%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20I%20was%20three%20years%20old.%20We%20settled%20in%20Nashville%20because%20my%20parents%20had%20contacts%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20undocumented%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20know%20it%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20my%20parents%20and%20I%20had%20to%20work%20very%20hard%20to%20earn%20a%20living%2C%20and%20we%20were%20always%20fearful%20of%20deportation.%20In%202013%2C%20at%2022%2C%20I%20applied%20for%20DACA%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaca-recipient-jaime-avalos-juarez-mexico-immigration-ice-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeferred%20action%20for%20childhood%20arrivals%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20was%20given%20a%20work%20authorization%20card%2C%20enabling%20me%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20in%20nursing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20grateful%20for%20the%20opportunity%20I've%20been%20given%20to%20work%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20in%20a%20society%20where%20Dreamers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20term%20for%20people%20protected%20under%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdesantis-wants-to-eliminate-college-tuition-for-undocumented-students-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDACA%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20used%20as%20political%20pawns%2C%20I%20think%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20for%20others%20like%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aec4587a-a880-46af-ac14-6c1815e132ce%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20family%20hustled%20hard%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20arriving%20in%20the%20US%2C%20my%20dad%20got%20a%20job%20in%20construction%2C%20which%20involved%20hard%20labor%2C%20hot%20summers%2C%20and%20crazy%20winters.%20My%20mum%20cleaned%20homes%20and%20offices.%20Neither%20of%20them%20knew%20English%2C%20but%20they%20were%20very%20resourceful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20from%20the%20bottom.%20I%20remember%20sharing%20apartments%20with%20other%20families%2C%20sleeping%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20and%20roaches.%20Then%2C%20my%20parents%20scraped%20up%20enough%20money%20to%20get%20into%20a%20trailer%20home%20where%20I%20grew%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20childhood%20with%20playtime%20but%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20time.%20When%20I%20wasn't%20in%20school%2C%20I%20helped%20my%20mum%20with%20food%20and%20cleaning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20know%20we%20were%20undocumented%20or%20what%20that%20meant%20until%20my%20parents%20told%20me%20when%20I%20was%20around%2010%20years%20old.%20As%20I%20grew%20up%2C%20I%20wondered%20why%20my%20parents%20had%20to%20work%20so%20hard%20and%20noticed%20we%20always%20had%20less%20than%20other%20people.%20I%20didn't%20understand%20why%20we%20always%20