0to%20go%20shopping.%20The%20handful%20of%20vendors%20at%20Arriba%20Juntos%2C%20Spanish%20for%20%26quot%3Bupward%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20are%20mostly%20immigrants%20trying%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20rising%20costs%20of%20rent%20and%20groceries.%20Since%20white%20shoppers%20seldom%20visit%20the%20market%2C%20one%20of%20the%20vendors%20suspected%20that%20the%20investigators%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewere%20undercover%20cops.%20Sure%20enough%2C%20uniformed%20officers%20with%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Police%20Department%20soon%20descended%20on%20the%20market's%20stalls%20and%20without%20a%20warrant%20arrested%20two%20women%20who%20were%20selling%20bras%20for%20%2420%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVeronica%20Lumbreras-Villanueva%2C%2040%2C%20and%20her%20mother-in-law%2C%20Deysi%20Ramirez%2C%2059%2C%20told%20the%20police%20they%20had%20purchased%20the%20bras%20from%20another%20flea%20market.%20But%20the%20garments%20still%20had%20their%20price%20tags%20%E2%80%94%20a%20sign%20that%20they'd%20probably%20been%20stolen%20at%20some%20point.%20The%20women%20had%20only%20%2479%20in%20cash%20on%20them%2C%20but%20the%20police%20valued%20their%20collection%20of%20267%20bras%20at%20%2416%2C000%2C%20the%20full%20retail%20value%20of%20the%20merchandise%20at%20Victoria's%20Secret.%20Brooke%20Jenkins%2C%20San%20Francisco's%20district%20attorney%2C%20accused%20Lumbreras-Villanueva%20and%20Ramirez%20of%20taking%20part%20in%20a%20%26quot%3BMission%20District%20fencing%20operation%2C%26quot%3B%20an%20alleged%20criminal%20enterprise%20she%20claimed%20incentivizes%20%26quot%3Borganized%20retail%20theft.%26quot%3B%20If%20convicted%20of%20the%20felony%20charges%2C%20the%20women%20could%20face%20more%20than%20three%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20the%20COVID%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20drugstore%20chains%2C%20luxury%20retailers%2C%20and%20department%20stores%20across%20the%20country%20have%20been%20working%20more%20closely%20with%20local%20prosecutors%20to%20imprison%20people%20in%20response%20to%20a%20wave%20of%20%26quot%3Bsmash%20and%20grab%26quot%3B%20thefts.%20In%202021%2C%20during%20Black%20Friday%20weekend%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area%2C%20more%20than%2080%20people%20swarmed%20a%20Nordstrom%20in%20Walnut%20Creek.%20Cameras%20captured%20another%20group%20fleeing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flouis-vuitton-spacex-rocket-may-happen-bernard-arnault-elon-musk-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELouis%20Vuitton%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20and%20a%20third%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esmashing%20the%20glass%20at%20a%20Sam's%20Jewelers%20in%20Hayward.%20Even%20though%20retailers%20nationwide%20reported%20little%2C%20if%20any%2C%20overall%20increase%20in%20lost%20inventory%2C%20it%20became%20common%20in%20major%20cities%20to%20hear%20reports%20of%20people%20brazenly%20stuffing%20merchandise%20into%20bags%20and%20walking%20out%20in%20full%20view%20of%20shoppers%20and%20employees.%20Many%20chains%2C%20including%20CVS%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarget-return-policy-update-fraud-abuse-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETarget%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20began%20locking%20their%20wares%20behind%20plastic%20shields%2C%20requiring%20shoppers%20to%20search%20understaffed%20stores%20for%20an%20employee%20to%20help%20them%20purchase%20items%20as%20simple%20as%20razors%20or%20Tide%20Pods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERetailers%20and%20prosecutors%20responded%20to%20the%20thefts%20with%20the%20kind%20of%20coordinated%20crackdown%20usually%20reserved%20for%20terrorists%20and%20drug%20cartels.%20Arguing%20that%20the%20epidemic%20of%20thefts%20is%20being%20orchestrated%20by%20high-level%20crime%20rings%2C%20the%20retail%20industry%20successfully%20lobbied%209%20states%20in%202023%20to%20up%20the%20penalties%20for%20what%20it%20calls%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-we-dont-actually-know-whether-retail-theft-big-problem-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorganized%20retail%20crime%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20to%20prosecute%20it%20aggressively.%20Last%20fall%2C%20Sen.%20Chuck%20Grassley%20stood%20outside%20the%20Capitol%20flanked%20by%20leaders%20of%20the%20National%20Retail%20Federation%20to%20introduce%20a%20bill%20that%20would%20make%20organized%20retail%20theft%20a%20federal%20crime.%20Even%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%20has%20gotten%20involved.%20Organized%20retail%20crime%20%26quot%3Bis%20not%20shoplifting%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20agency%20says%20on%20its%20website%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20these%20crimes%20are%20not%20victimless.%26quot%3B%20Some%20lawmakers%20and%20industry%20lobbyists%20have%20gone%20so%20far%20as%20to%20claim%20that%20retail%20theft%20has%20direct%20links%20to%20human%20trafficking%20and%20domestic%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENowhere%20has%20the%20industry%20been%20more%20successful%20in%20selling%20its%20War%20on%20Retail%20Crime%20than%20in%20California.%20The%20state%20passed%20a%20law%20in%202018%20defining%20organized%20retail%20theft%20as%20two%20or%20more%20people%20who%20steal%20%26quot%3Bwith%20the%20intent%20to%20sell%2C%20exchange%2C%20or%20return%20the%20merchandise%20for%20value.%26quot%3B%20If%20the%20total%20amount%20of%20the%20stolen%20merchandise%20reaches%20%24950%2C%20the%20theft%20becomes%20a%20felony%2C%20and%20two-time%20offenders%20can%20face%20up%20to%20three%20years%20in%20prison.%20A%20new%20measure%20on%20the%20ballot%20in%20California%20this%20November%20would%20eliminate%20the%20%24950%20requirement%20on%20the%20third%20offense%2C%20effectively%20creating%20a%20%26quot%3Bthree%20strikes%26quot%3B%20rule%20for%20shoplifting.%20If%20you%20and%20a%20friend%20keep%20ripping%20off%20your%20local%20drugstore%2C%20you%20could%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20be%20participating%20in%20felony%20organized%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221802%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Police%20patrol%20a%20Gucci%20store%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f57abede59ade1a3b4cb2c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221190%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFacing%20a%20nationwide%20wave%20of%20%26quot%3Bsmash%20and%20grab%26quot%3B%20thefts%2C%20retailers%20are%20working%20with%20prosecutors%20on%20the%20kind%20of%20full-scale%2C%20coordinated%20crackdown%20usually%20reserved%20for%20terrorists%20and%20drug%20cartels.%3Cp%3ESan%20Francisco%20Chronicle%2FHearst%20Newspapers%20via%20Getty%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20there%20have%20been%20a%20handful%20of%20cases%20where%20people%20have%20been%20convicted%20of%20organizing%20multi-million%20dollar%20thefts%20and%20recruiting%20others%20to%20steal%20for%20them.%20But%20after%20thousands%20of%20arrests%2C%20prosecutors%20have%20shown%20no%20evidence%20that%20the%20nationwide%20wave%20of%20shoplifting%20is%20being%20secretly%20coordinated%20by%20mobsters%20or%20terrorists.%20In%20the%20San%20Francisco%20bra%20arrest%2C%20there%20appears%20to%20be%20nothing%20even%20linking%20the%20women%20from%20the%20flea%20market%20to%20an%20actual%20theft.%20Last%20February%2C%20three%20months%20after%20the%20felony%20charges%20were%20filed%20and%20the%20women's%20names%20were%20splashed%20across%20local%20news%20outlets%20suggesting%20they%20had%20links%20to%20organized%20criminals%2C%20a%20prosecutor%20with%20the%20district%20attorney's%20office%20appeared%20to%20be%20struggling%20to%20build%20a%20case.%20The%20prosecutor%20emailed%20investigators%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvictorias-secret-rise-and-fall-history-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVictoria's%20Secret%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20plead%20for%20assistance.%20%26quot%3BHad%20anyone%20from%20Victoria%20Secret%20(or%20other%20retailers)%20observed%20Ramirez%20and%20Villanueva%20selling%20VS%20merchandise%20before%2010%2F7%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20prosecutor%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20crackdown%20by%20industry%20and%20law%20enforcement%20has%20effectively%20criminalized%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epoverty.%20Attorneys%2C%20defendants%2C%20and%20experts%20familiar%20with%20the%20surge%20of%20prosecutions%20report%20that%20retail%20theft%20is%20overwhelmingly%20committed%20by%20people%20in%20serious%20need%2C%20especially%20those%20lacking%20housing%20or%20suffering%20from%20drug%20addiction%20or%20mental%20illness.%20The%20result%2C%20as%20with%20the%20government's%20long-running%20%26quot%3Bwars%26quot%3B%20on%20drugs%20and%20terrorism%2C%20has%20been%20a%20dragnet%20that%20ensnares%20a%20lot%20of%20small%20fish%20who%20are%20then%20presented%20to%20the%20world%20as%20big%20catches.%20Several%20others%20facing%20felony%20charges%20for%20what%20the%20San%20Francisco%20police%20describe%20as%20%26quot%3Bprolific%20Organized%20Retail%20Crime%26quot%3B%20are%20minors%2C%20including%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanfranciscopolice.org%2Fnews%2Fsfpd-arrests-prolific-organized-retail-crime-suspect-23-150%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E14-year-old%20girl%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sanfranciscopolice.org%2Fnews%2Fsfpd-arrests-violent-and-prolific-organized-retail-crime%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E13-year-old%20boy%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20homeless%20woman%20in%20jail%20who%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20felony%20organized%20retail%20theft%20tells%20me%20she%20steals%20out%20of%20desperation.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20hard%20for%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20steal%20because%20I%20can't%20read%20or%20write.%26quot%3B%20On%20a%20crowded%20sidewalk%20in%20the%20Mission%20District%2C%20a%20group%20of%20people%20are%20selling%20pants%20with%20the%20anti-theft%20tags%20still%20attached%20and%20other%20items.%20Two%20homeless%20men%20with%20the%20group%20say%20they%20sometimes%20steal%20from%20Walgreens%20and%20Target.%20They%20scoff%20at%20the%20idea%20of%20retail%20theft%20being%20an%20organized%20crime.%20%26quot%3BNot%20even%20close%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20one.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20bunch%20of%20fucking%20crackheads.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20retailers%20and%20government%20officials%2C%20retail%20theft%20can%20be%20a%20convenient%20scapegoat%20for%20the%20woes%20that%20have%20been%20facing%20American%20cities%20and%20malls%20since%20the%20onset%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20In%202021%2C%20videos%20of%20smash-and-grabs%20at%20chain%20stores%20began%20playing%20regularly%20in%20national%20news%20segments%20about%20San%20Francisco's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-francisco-doom-loop-fix-american-city-housing-transit-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Edoom%20loop%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Retailers%20were%20quick%20to%20blame%20crime%20rings%20for%20widespread%20store%20closures%2C%20and%20law%20enforcement%20was%20quick%20to%20agree.%20Last%20October%2C%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20sent%20%24267%20million%20to%20cities%20across%20California%20to%20increase%20arrests%20of%20organized%20retail%20crime%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20crackdown%20has%20escalated%20dramatically.%20In%20April%2C%20after%20a%2025-year-old%20and%20two%20teenagers%20in%20Napa%20County%20were%20accused%20of%20walking%20out%20of%20a%20Lululemon%20with%20%2425%2C000%20worth%20of%20athleisure%2C%20officers%20from%20three%20police%20departments%20and%20a%20California%20Highway%20Patrol%20helicopter%20pursued%20them%20in%20a%20high-speed%20chase%20to%20retrieve%20the%20runaway%20leggings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20big%20chunk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgov-newsom-says-hes-worried-californias-ai-bill-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENewson's%3C%2Fa%3E%20initiative%20%E2%80%94%20%2417%20million%20%E2%80%94%20went%20to%20the%20police%20department%20and%20the%20district%20attorney's%20office%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20which%20retailers%20often%20call%20the%20focal%20point%20of%20organized%20retail%20theft%20in%20America.%20The%20grant%20centers%20on%20patrolling%20Union%20Square%2C%20the%20city's%20version%20of%20Rodeo%20Drive%2C%20featuring%20luxury%20retailers%20like%20Saks%2C%20Louis%20Vuitton%2C%20and%20Chanel.%20The%20crimes%2C%20because%20of%20their%20supposedly%20organized%20nature%2C%20are%20handled%20by%20the%20white-collar%20division%20of%20the%20prosecutor's%20office.%20But%20those%20on%20the%20ground%20paint%20a%20different%20picture%20of%20the%20thefts.%20A%20security%20guard%20at%20a%20Victoria's%20Secret%20in%20San%20Francisco%20tells%20me%20that%20most%20of%20the%20people%20who%20steal%20from%20the%20store%20are%20teenagers%2C%20or%20middle-aged%20men%20he%20assumes%20are%20looking%20to%20buy%20drugs.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20not%20sophisticated%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20guard%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227928%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Anti-theft%20case%20at%20a%20convenience%20store%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f57705de59ade1a3b4c76d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225285%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMany%20chains%20have%20locked%20their%20wares%20behind%20plastic%20shields%2C%20requiring%20shoppers%20to%20seek%20assistance%20to%20purchase%20items%20as%20simple%20as%20razors%20or%20Tide%20Pods.%3Cp%3EANGELA%20WEISS%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20National%20Retail%20Federation%20insists%20that%20homeless%20people%20are%20recruited%20by%20criminal%20organizations%20to%20steal%2C%20and%20portrays%20itself%20as%20trying%20to%20assist%20the%20very%20people%20its%20members%20are%20working%20to%20lock%20up.%20%26quot%3BThe%20goal%20is%20to%20get%20them%20the%20help%20they%20need%20for%20health%20and%20services%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20David%20Johnston%2C%20the%20federation's%20vice%20president%20of%20asset%20protection%20and%20retail%20operations.%20But%20some%20retailers%20have%20made%20clear%20that%20they're%20targeting%20homeless%20people%20for%20other%20reasons.%20At%20an%20industry%20talk%20last%20year%2C%20an%20asset-protection%20executive%20for%20Kroger%20said%20homeless%20people%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bdrug-afflicted%26quot%3B%20were%20among%20the%20most%20%26quot%3Bextreme%26quot%3B%20and%20violent%20shoplifters.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20retailer%20in%20America%20I%20think%20faces%20similar%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BNo%20longer%20are%20we%20going%20to%20allow%20that%20population%20to%20rule%20our%20stores.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20evidence%20to%20suggest%20that%20homeless%20people%20are%20more%20violent%20than%20others%20who%20commit%20retail%20theft.%20The%20homeless%20people%20I%20talked%20to%20said%20they%20steal%20from%20corporate%20chains%2C%20which%20often%20prohibit%20employees%20from%20confronting%20shoplifters%2C%20specifically%20to%20%3Cem%3Eavoid%3C%2Fem%3E%20violence.%20In%20reality%2C%20homeless%20people%20suspected%20of%20retail%20theft%20may%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20victims%20of%20violence.%20In%20separate%20cases%20in%20San%20Francisco%20and%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20security%20guards%20fatally%20shot%20unarmed%20homeless%20people%20suspected%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwalgreens-store-theft-shoplifting-employee-catch-thieves-drugstore-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshoplifting%20at%20Walgreens%3C%2Fa%3E%20stores.%20The%20guard%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20was%20charged%20with%20murder.%20But%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20the%20district%20attorney%20refused%20to%20prosecute%20the%20guard%2C%20saying%20he%20had%20feared%20for%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESan%20Francisco's%20jails%20are%20starting%20to%20fill%20up%20with%20people%20accused%20of%20stealing%20from%20leading%20retailers.%20Of%20the%2090%20women%20incarcerated%20at%20San%20Francisco's%20County%20Jail%20No.%202%20in%20April%2C%20seven%20faced%20charges%20of%20organized%20retail%20theft.%20Shalia%20Brown%2C%20a%2025-year-old%20arrested%20in%20a%20sting%20outside%20Walgreens%2C%20has%20been%20incarcerated%20without%20bail%20for%2011%20months.%20Because%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20her%20case%2C%20she's%20being%20held%20%26quot%3Bbehind%20the%20door%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20she%20can't%20interact%20with%20anyone%20besides%20her%20cellmates.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20I'm%20going%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrown%20spent%20her%20teenage%20years%20in%20foster-care%20institutions.%20At%2021%2C%20after%20moving%20into%20an%20%2485-a-night%20motel%20room%20in%20Oakland%20with%20her%20young%20son%2C%20she%20struggled%20to%20find%20childcare%20and%20a%20job.%20Her%20neighbors%20told%20her%20about%20an%20easier%20way%20to%20make%20money%3A%20going%20together%20in%20small%20groups%20to%20shoplift%20from%20chain%20stores%20like%20CVS%20or%20Walgreens%2C%20where%20corporate%20policy%20forbids%20employees%20from%20getting%20physical%20with%20suspected%20thieves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20Brown%20stole%20from%20a%20CVS%2C%20she%20was%20terrified%3A%20She%20just%20wanted%20to%20get%20diapers%20for%20her%20son.%20But%20it%20was%20so%20easy%20that%20she%20started%20going%20back%20regularly.%20Afterwards%2C%20she%20and%20other%20%26quot%3Bboosters%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20street%20would%20sell%20stolen%20goods%20at%20a%20discount%2C%20making%20as%20much%20as%20%24500%20a%20day.%20To%20protect%20herself%20from%20being%20robbed%2C%20she%20started%20carrying%20a%20toy%20gun%20that%20shoots%20water-gel%20pellets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20October%2C%20in%20a%20run%20on%20CVS%2C%20Brown%20planned%20to%20get%20her%20son%20diapers%20for%20the%20night.%20But%20a%20CVS%20employee%20named%20Thomas%20Riddle%20tried%20to%20stop%20her.%20In%20surveillance%20footage%20of%20the%20confrontation%2C%20Riddle%20pulls%20Brown%20to%20the%20ground.%20Brown%20stands%20up%2C%20backs%20away%2C%20and%20pulls%20out%20the%20toy%20gun.%20Riddle%20responds%20by%20punching%20and%20kicking%20her%2C%20until%20others%20appear%20to%20intervene%2C%20allowing%20Brown%20to%20get%20away.%20(In%20a%20court%20hearing%2C%20he%20said%20he%20was%20fired%20two%20weeks%20later.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20weeks%20later%2C%20Brown%20tried%20to%20steal%20from%20a%20Walgreens.%20This%20time%2C%20she%20and%20four%20others%20were%20arrested%20by%20undercover%20police%20officers%20who%20were%20parked%20outside%20the%20store.%20With%20the%20surveillance%20footage%20from%20other%20stores%20at%20their%20disposal%20and%20a%20special%20task%20force%20devoted%20to%20retail%20theft%2C%20the%20police%20were%20able%20to%20identify%20Brown%20and%20connect%20her%20to%20other%20incidents.%20The%20district%20attorney's%20office%20charged%20her%20with%20felony%20organized%20retail%20theft%2C%20along%20with%20charges%20of%20robbery%2C%20assault%2C%20and%20use%20of%20a%20deadly%20weapon%20related%20to%20the%20CVS%20fight%20with%20the%20toy%20gun.%20If%20convicted%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe%20faces%20up%20to%20nine%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20San%20Francisco%20public%20defender's%20office%20says%20it's%20common%20for%20prosecutors%20to%20slap%20retail-theft%20suspects%20with%20multiple%20charges%2C%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20argue%20that%20they%20should%20remain%20in%20jail%20until%20their%20trials%20and%20serve%20more%20time.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20this%20idea%20of%20overcharging%20or%20charging%20everything%20on%20the%20board%2C%20both%20to%20file%20a%20detention%20motion%20and%20to%20make%20sure%20something%20sticks%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Elizabeth%20Camacho%2C%20a%20deputy%20public%20defender.%20She%20also%20notes%20how%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscholar.smu.edu%2Fbusiness_marketing_research%2F32%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eracialized%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20policing%20of%20organized%20retail%20theft%20has%20become.%20Of%20the%2047%20people%20her%20office%20has%20represented%20since%202019%20on%20charges%20of%20organized%20retail%20theft%2C%2038%20are%20Black.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ERetail%20theft%20itself%20may%20not%20be%20highly%20sophisticated%2C%20but%20the%20arsenal%20of%20surveillance%20tools%20that%20retailers%20are%20developing%20to%20track%20and%20prosecute%20retail%20theft%20certainly%20is.%20In%20January%2C%20the%20chipmaker%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchip-tsmc-taiwan-semiconductor-trillion-market-cap-nvidia-ai-asml-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ENvidia%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20announced%20it%20was%20collaborating%20with%20more%20than%20500%20tech%20startups%20to%20build%20an%20AI-based%20%26quot%3Breal-time%20solution%20for%20combating%20and%20preventing%20organized%20retail%20crime.%26quot%3B%20FaceFirst%20makes%20facial-recognition%20technology%20for%20superstores%2C%20while%20Flock%20Safety%20advertises%20license-plate%20readers%20to%20build%20a%20virtual%20%26quot%3Bperimeter%20around%20your%20parking%20lot%20to%20proactively%20address%20theft%20and%20organized%20retail%20crime%20threats.%26quot%3B%20Some%20Lululemon%20clothes%20are%20embedded%20with%20a%20chip%20that%20allows%20security%20guards%20to%20follow%20them%20in%20real%20time.%20That's%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20extensive%20in-house%20%26quot%3Basset%20protection%26quot%3B%20teams%20that%20chains%20often%20employ%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20now%20wear%20%3Cu%3Ebody%20cameras%3C%2Fu%3E.%20Big-box%20stores%2C%20it%20appears%2C%20are%20the%20new%20Big%20Brother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20surveillance%20efforts%20by%20retailers%20are%20playing%20a%20central%20role%20in%20the%20crackdown%20on%20retail%20theft.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20impossible%20for%20law%20enforcement%20to%20do%20our%20job%20without%20these%20retailers%20%E2%80%94%20they%20do%20so%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Capt.%20Jeff%20Loftin%20of%20the%20California%20Highway%20Patrol%2C%20whose%20own%20organized-retail-crime%20division%2C%20launched%20in%202019%2C%20has%20made%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.ca.gov%2F2024%2F09%2F18%2Fchp-retail-crime-task-force-makes-1000-arrests-recovers-7-8-million-in-stolen-goods-this-year%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earrests%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20organized-retail-crime%20investigator%20for%20a%20major%20clothing%20retailer%2C%20who%20spoke%20on%20the%20condition%20of%20anonymity%2C%20says%20his%20job%20includes%20following%20suspects%20to%20where%20they%20live%2C%20collecting%20video%20surveillance%20from%20other%20retailers%2C%20and%20presenting%20criminal%20cases%20to%20district%20attorneys.%20The%20investigator%2C%20who%20previously%20worked%20at%20Target%20for%2011%20years%2C%20says%20the%20company%20barred%20employees%20from%20intervening%20with%20shoplifters%20specifically%20so%20it%20could%20build%20felony%20cases%20against%20repeat%20offenders.%20Rather%20than%20watching%20suspects%20get%20arrested%20and%20released%20on%20a%20single%20charge%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20stores%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20them%20over%20time%20and%20then%20present%20the%20case%20to%20the%20DA%2C%20hoping%20that%20the%20shoplifter%20will%20serve%20time.%20A%20Target%20spokesperson%20speaking%20on%20background%20said%20that%20is%20not%20the%20company's%20policy%2C%20but%20declined%20to%20share%20what%20Target's%20policy%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22san%20francisco%20homeless%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F594d54a0d084cc163f8b4b9f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221405%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThere's%20no%20evidence%20that%20homeless%20people%20are%20more%20violent%20than%20others%20who%20commit%20retail%20theft%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they're%20actually%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20victims%20of%20violence.%3Cp%3EEric%20Risberg%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20case%20in%20San%20Francisco%20also%20seems%20to%20illustrate%20this%20has%20been%20a%20case-building%20tactic.%20In%202020%2C%20a%2043-year-old%20woman%20named%20Aziza%20Graves%20started%20picking%20up%20items%20at%20a%20Target%2C%20scanning%20them%20at%20a%20self-checkout%2C%20and%20inserting%20a%20single%20penny%20as%20payment.%20Staffers%20tried%20asking%20her%20to%20return%20the%20items%2C%20but%20she%20ignored%20them%20and%20kept%20coming%20back%2C%20paying%20with%20a%20penny%20each%20time.%20Employees%20started%20to%20leave%20her%20alone.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20come%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20Miss%20Graves%20was%20not%20worth%20following%20closely%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Target%20asset-protection%20manager%20testified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Target%20continued%20to%20follow%20Graves%20closely%2C%20deploying%20an%20internal%20surveillance%20system%20that%20filmed%20her%20using%20the%20self-checkout%20machine%20and%20generated%20case%20reports%20for%20everything%20she%20was%20accused%20of%20taking%2C%20from%20Tide%20Pods%20to%2025-cent%20shopping%20bags.%20By%20the%20time%20she%20was%20charged%2C%20Target%20investigators%20said%2C%20she%20had%20stolen%20more%20than%20%2440%2C000%20worth%20of%20items%20over%20the%20course%20of%20100%20thefts.%20After%20a%20four-week%20trial%2C%20Graves%20was%20convicted%20of%20felony%20grand%20theft%20and%2052%20counts%20of%20misdemeanor%20petty%20theft.%20Local%20business%20leaders%20and%20officials%20touted%20the%20case%20as%20evidence%20of%20theft%20run%20rampant.%20People%20like%20Graves%20%26quot%3Bcommit%20egregious%20thefts%20through%20brazen%20and%20repeated%20conduct%2C%26quot%3B%20Brooke%20Jenkins%2C%20the%20San%20Francisco%20district%20attorney%2C%20declared%20in%20a%20press%20release%20celebrating%20the%20conviction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20Jenkins%20neglected%20to%20mention%20in%20her%20many%20interviews%20and%20statements%20about%20the%20case%20is%20that%20Graves%20was%20surviving%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eon%20food%20stamps%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20despite%20being%20ruled%20competent%20to%20stand%20trial%2C%20appeared%20to%20be%20unstable.%20Graves%20has%20repeatedly%20insisted%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20that%20pennies%20have%20infinite%20value%2C%20meaning%20her%20payments%20at%20Target%20far%20exceeded%20the%20value%20of%20the%20items%20she%20took.%20When%20I%20speak%20with%20her%2C%20Graves%20tells%20me%20she's%20concerned%20the%20judge%20in%20her%20case%20might%20be%20a%20hypnotist%20from%20Maury%20Povich's%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20June%2C%20at%20the%20sentencing%20hearing%20for%20Graves%2C%20the%20prosecutor's%20conduct%20backfires.%20At%20the%20Hall%20of%20Justice%2C%20the%20district%20attorney's%20office%20asks%20Judge%20Jeffrey%20Ross%20to%20sentence%20Graves%20to%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20in%20prison%2C%20or%20order%20her%20to%20pay%20%2440%2C000%20in%20restitution%20to%20Target%20if%20she%20is%20put%20on%20probation.%20Instead%2C%20Ross%20tells%20prosecutors%20he's%20distressed%20by%20the%20statements%20the%20office%20made%20tying%20Graves%20to%20other%20retail%20theft%20in%20the%20city.%20%26quot%3BFor%20the%20People%20in%20a%20press%20release%20to%20suggest%20that%20Ms.%20Graves'%20issues%20are%20similar%20to%20those%20are%20really%20quite%20an%20inappropriate%20role%20for%20the%20prosecutor%20to%20play%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20The%20judge%20refuses%20to%20send%20her%20back%20to%20jail%2C%20instead%20sentencing%20her%20to%20two%20years%20on%20mandatory%20supervision%2C%20and%20ordering%20her%20to%20pay%20%2422%2C000.%20A%20case%20three%20years%20in%20the%20making%20comes%20to%20an%20anticlimactic%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20she%20leaves%20the%20courtroom%2C%20Graves%20is%20followed%20by%20a%20local%20reporter%20from%20ABC%20News%2C%20who%20asks%20if%20she's%20happy%20not%20to%20be%20going%20to%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20sorry%20about%20what%20happened%20to%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Graves%20responds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reporter%20tells%20her%20he%20has%20no%20idea%20what%20she's%20talking%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20all%20the%20effort%20spent%20prosecuting%20it%2C%20there's%20virtually%20no%20concrete%20evidence%20that%20retail%20theft%20%E2%80%94%20organized%20or%20otherwise%20%E2%80%94%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%20Data%20on%20retail%20theft%20provided%20to%20law%20enforcement%20and%20lawmakers%20comes%20exclusively%20from%20corporate%20retailers%2C%20or%20organizations%20funded%20by%20them%2C%20and%20is%20not%20independently%20vetted.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20National%20Retail%20Federation%20was%20forced%20to%20retract%20its%20claim%20that%20organized%20retail%20theft%20cost%20its%20members%20%26quot%3Bnearly%20half%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20%2494.5%20billion%20in%20lost%20inventory%20in%202021.%20One%20researcher%20put%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F08%2Fbusiness%2Forganized-shoplifting-retail-crime-theft-retraction.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eactual%20figure%20closer%20to%205%25%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Even%20the%20guy%20who%20says%20he%20coined%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Borganized%20retail%20crime%26quot%3B%20can't%20say%20how%20much%20is%20lost%20to%20it.%20%26quot%3BNobody%20knows%20and%20probably%20will%20never%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Read%20Hayes%2C%20who%20founded%20the%20industry-funded%20nonprofit%20Loss%20Prevention%20Research%20Council%20after%20retailers%20recruited%20him%20to%20back%20their%20anti-theft%20campaign%20with%20research.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20measuring%20the%20wind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20hasn't%20stopped%20major%20retailers%20from%20blaming%20organized%20theft%20for%20their%20post-pandemic%20store%20closures.%20Victoria's%20Secret%2C%20which%20shuttered%20250%20stores%20in%202020%2C%20said%20last%20year%20that%20organized%20retail%20crime%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20significant%20component%20of%20the%20shrinkage%20we%20experience.%26quot%3B%20But%20lost%20inventory%20is%20far%20from%20the%20company's%20biggest%20problem.%20Its%20market%20share%20has%20been%20dwindling%20for%20years.%20Investors%20and%20analysts%20blame%20the%20decline%20on%20the%20death%20of%20shopping%20malls%2C%20the%20company's%20out-of-touch%20marketing%20campaigns%2C%20and%20the%20public-relations%20crisis%20sparked%20by%20the%20close%20ties%20between%20the%20CEO%20of%20its%20former%20parent%20company%20and%20Jeffrey%20Epstein.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20shoppers%20have%20found%20radio-frequency-identification%20chips%20on%20the%20tags%20sewn%20into%20Victoria's%20Secret%20bras%2C%20prompting%20online%20conspiracy%20theories%20that%20they%20were%20being%20used%20to%20spy%20on%20customers.%20A%20company%20spokesperson%20responded%20in%202020%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20only%20use%20this%20technology%20in%20our%20back%20room%20and%20sales%20floors%20to%20help%20us%20manage%20inventory%20so%20that%20our%20associates%20can%20efficiently%20support%20our%20customers'%20needs.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20chips%20were%20key%20in%20filing%20charges%20against%20Veronica%20Lumbreras-Villanueva%20and%20Deysi%20Ramirez%2C%20the%20two%20women%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20Mission%20District%20flea-market%20case.%20The%20police%20say%20an%20investigator%20from%20Victoria's%20Secret%20was%20able%20to%20flag%20the%20table%20where%20the%20women%20were%20selling%20bras%20because%20her%20scanner%20detected%20that%20the%20items%20%26quot%3Bhad%20never%20passed%20a%20point%20of%20sale.%26quot%3B%20There%20is%20no%20footage%20of%20the%20woman%20stealing%20from%20a%20store.%20Prosecutors%20appear%20to%20be%20relying%20solely%20on%20the%20ID%20chips%20from%20Victoria's%20Secret.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20preliminary%20hearing%20for%20the%20two%20women%20is%20scheduled%20to%20take%20place%20on%20October%203%2C%20nearly%20a%20year%20after%20they%20were%20arrested.%20The%20DA's%20office%20would%20not%20comment%20on%20the%20case.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20Victoria's%20Secret%20said%20%26quot%3Bwe%20take%20matters%20of%20theft%20seriously%20and%20work%20closely%20and%20in%20cooperation%20with%20the%20appropriate%20authorities%20on%20these%20types%20of%20investigations.%20We%20will%20prosecute%20offenders%20to%20the%20full%20extent%20of%20the%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVictoria's%20Secret%20is%20not%20alone%20in%20its%20prosecutorial%20zeal.%20Many%20companies%20are%20pushing%20for%20hefty%20restitution%20payments%20in%20theft%20cases%20%E2%80%94%20not%20for%20employees%20injured%20or%20traumatized%20by%20shoplifters%2C%20but%20for%20their%20own%20losses.%20One%20homeless%20woman%20I%20spoke%20with%2C%20who%20spent%20eight%20months%20in%20jail%20for%20stealing%20items%20from%20Bath%20and%20Body%20Works%20and%20selling%20them%20on%20the%20street%2C%20leaves%20jail%20owing%20%2415%2C000%20in%20restitution%20to%20the%20retail%20chain.%20And%20when%20defendants%20request%20to%20be%20placed%20in%20alternative%20courts%2C%20where%20they%20can%20receive%20counseling%20for%20addiction%20and%20other%20problems%2C%20stores%20and%20prosecutors%20have%20insisted%20that%20they%20do%20time.%20In%20a%20case%20involving%20a%20suspect%20accused%20of%20stealing%20jeans%20from%20a%20San%20Francisco%20Bloomingdale's%2C%20the%20prosecutor%20received%20an%20email%20from%20Alto%2C%20a%20global%20%26quot%3Bvictim%20advocate%26quot%3B%20for%20corporate%20clients%20like%20Walgreens%20and%20Target.%20%26quot%3BBloomingdale's%20is%20against%20this%20case%20being%20deferred%20to%20Mental%20Health%20Court%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20defendant%20%26quot%3Bcaused%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20loss%20and%20trauma%20for%20the%20store%20and%20its%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20Alto%20advised%20the%20prosecutor.%20%26quot%3BI%20wanted%20to%20restate%20that%20Bloomingdale's%20is%20seeking%20jail%20time%20with%20restitution%20granted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228110%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gavin%20Newsom%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66f57246de59ade1a3b4c322%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20has%20provided%20California%20cities%20with%20%24267%20million%20and%20signed%2010%20new%20bills%20into%20law%20to%20bolster%20the%20prosecution%20of%20organized%20retail%20crime.%20%3Cp%3EAnadolu%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20the%20War%20on%20Retail%20Crime%20rages%20on.%20In%20August%2C%20while%20presiding%20over%20a%20display%20of%20buckets%20at%20a%20Home%20Depot%2C%20Gavin%20Newsom%20signed%2010%20bills%20into%20law%20promising%20to%20further%20increase%20the%20prosecution%20of%20retail%20theft.%20Meanwhile%2C%20some%20of%20the%20same%20stores%20identified%20as%20victims%20in%20retail-theft%20cases%20stand%20accused%20of%20exacerbating%20the%20very%20problem%20they're%20complaining%20about.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20CVS%2C%20Walgreens%2C%20and%20Walmart%20have%20been%20required%20to%20pay%20billions%20of%20dollars%20to%20state%20attorneys%20general%20to%20settle%20claims%20that%20they%20fueled%20the%20opioid%20crisis.%20In%202022%2C%20a%20survey%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Fstory%2F2022-01-11%2F2-out-of-3-kroger-workers-struggle-to-afford-food-housing-survey-finds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etwo-thirds%20of%20Kroger%20employees%20struggled%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20afford%20food%20and%20housing.%20If%20retail%20theft%20is%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20it%20may%20have%20less%20to%20do%20with%20organized%20crime%20than%20with%20the%20refusal%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emajor%20retailers%20to%20pay%20a%20living%20wage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECuauhtemoc%20Ramirez%2C%20a%2020-year-old%20being%20held%20without%20bail%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%20was%20living%20in%20his%20car%20and%20struggling%20to%20quit%20alcohol%20and%20drugs%20when%20he%20was%20arrested.%20He%20is%20accused%20of%20being%20%26quot%3Bpart%20of%20an%20organized%20group%26quot%3B%20that%20stole%20more%20than%20%24100%2C000%20worth%20of%20products%20from%20Walgreens%2C%20Safeway%2C%20and%20other%20major%20retailers.%20He%20came%20to%20San%20Francisco%20because%20he%20heard%20it%20was%20a%20city%20that%20helps%20people%20in%20need.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20change%20my%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20go%20to%20trial%20and%20lose%2C%20it's%20six%20to%20eight%20years.%20I%20want%20the%20mental-health%20court.%20I'm%20in%20here%20not%20getting%20help.%26quot%3B%20Organized%20retail%20theft%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20just%20people%20from%20everywhere%20trying%20to%20feed%20their%20addiction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmy%20Martyn%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20covering%20labor%2C%20retail%2C%20and%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-war-organized-retail-crime-target-cvs-victorias-secret-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727690101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e8409fbf0250c21493a584%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-war-organized-retail-crime-target-cvs-victorias-secret-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Target%20and%20CVS%20call%20them%20criminal%20masterminds.%20Most%20are%20homeless%20or%20mentally%20ill.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Amy%20Martyn)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-war-organized-retail-crime-target-cvs-victorias-secret-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22UAE%20condemns%20'heinous'%20attack%20on%20ambassador's%20home%20in%20Sudan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727690010000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113813638%2Cimgsize-821899.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fuae-con