20a.m.%2C%20I%20was%20at%20the%20computer%20ready%20at%209%20a.m..%20Once%20I%20was%20flying%20to%20Tokyo%20and%20the%20fight%20was%20late%20in%20the%20day%2C%20but%20I%20wouldn't%20even%20go%20for%20a%20walk%20because%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20needed%20to%20stay%20home%20until%20I%20got%20into%20the%20cab%20to%20the%20airport%20because%20%26quot%3Byou%20don't%20know%20what%20might%20happen!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20three%20months%20on%20psilocybin%2C%20that%20neurosis%20was%20gone.%20I%20now%20log%20onto%20a%20meeting%20one%20minute%20before%20because%20I%20feel%20confident%20in%20my%20ability%20to%20cope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2207811cfc-f1f5-48ef-9578-26be77fdbdad%5C%22%3EI%20started%20to%20become%20aware%20of%20my%20limiting%20beliefs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20more%20space%20in%20my%20brain%2C%20which%20gave%20me%20enough%20distance%20from%20my%20thoughts%20to%20see%20them%20clearer.%20I%20started%20to%20become%20aware%20that%20some%20subconscious%20beliefs%20I%20had%20were%20making%20me%20feel%20bad%20about%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20that%20I%20had%20a%20huge%20fear%20of%20authority%2C%20which%20was%20likely%20a%20product%20of%20being%20raised%20in%20a%20very%20authoritarian%20environment.%20I%20had%20this%20belief%20that%20I%20always%20had%20to%20do%20what%20I%20was%20told%2C%20which%20had%20been%20limiting%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%20I%20was%20able%20to%20notice%20the%20pattern%20and%2C%20over%20time%2C%20reprogram%20my%20brain%20to%20respond%20differently.%20I%20became%20a%20bit%20of%20an%20explorer%2C%20looking%20out%20for%20blind%20spots%20and%20observing%20my%20tendencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f7050b7d-fc05-4de4-807f-60b0cf5ea924%5C%22%3EMy%20network%20really%20responded%20to%20my%20story%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20had%20a%20newsletter%20where%20I%20wrote%20about%20companies%20I%20thought%20people%20should%20invest%20in.%20But%20one%20day%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20write%