store%20Borsheims%2C%20a%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20subsidiary.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGoracke%20worked%20her%20way%20up%20from%20the%20store%20room%2C%20and%20Warren%20Buffett%20interviewed%20her%20for%20CEO.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20she%20talks%20to%20Buffett%20about%20everything%20from%20sports%20to%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20transcribed%20conversation%20with%20Karen%20Goracke%2C%20CEO%20and%20President%20of%20Borsheims%2C%20about%20her%20career%20and%20working%20with%20Warren%20Buffett.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20working%20as%20a%20sales%20associate%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fborsheims-warren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-jewelry-pandemic-inflation-karen-goracke-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBorsheims%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20jewelry%20store%20in%20Omaha%2C%20in%201988%20straight%20out%20of%20college.%20It%20seemed%20like%20a%20glamorous%20place%20to%20work.%20It%20was%20a%20big%20company%20run%20like%20a%20small%20family%20business.%20There%20was%20no%20inventory%2C%20and%20our%20accounting%20practices%20weren't%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20year%20later%2C%20in%201989%2C%20Warren%20Buffett's%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.berkshirehathaway.com%2Fletters%2F1989.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eacquired%20Borsheims%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20family%20that%20owned%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBerkshire%20Hathaway%20likes%20to%20buy%20successful%20companies.%20When%20they%20acquired%20Borsheims%2C%20they%20were%20pretty%20hands-off%20about%20the%20daily%20running%20of%20the%20company%2C%20with%20one%20caveat%3A%20We%20should%20have%20a%20controlled%20inventory%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b468e11b-6d89-449b-9b90-988ec80d6c40%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20promoted%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20I%20was%20young%2C%20they%20put%20me%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20inventory%20project.%20There%20were%20100%2C000%20pieces%20of%20inventory.%20I%20went%20through%20each%20item%20one%20by%20one%20to%20create%20a%20data%20entry.%20I'd%20handwrite%20a%20tag%20for%20it%2C%20put%20the%20tag%20on%20the%20item%2C%20and%20put%20it%20back%20in%20its%20case.%20I%20often%20had%20to%20ask%20the%20former%20owners%20how%20much%20some%20pieces%20cost%20because%20a%20lot%20of%20them%20had%20been%20bought%20in%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%20they%20gave%20me%20a%20team%20to%20help%20out.%20It%20took%20us%20a%20few%20years%2C%20but%20we%20got%20everything%20in%20a%20system%2C%20and%20had%20data%20we%20could%20use.%20I%20shared%20the%20data%20with%20the%20buying%20team%2C%20telling%20them%20where%20they%20were%20making%20money%20and%20where%20they%20had%20too%20much%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20knew%20Warren%20Buffett%20knew%20what%20I%20did%20because%20he%20wrote%20notes%20about%20the%20inventory%20saying%20it%20was%20looking%20good%20or%20needed%20improvement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20offered%20me%20a%20job%20as%20a%20watch%20buyer%2C%20which%20I%20took%20in%201996.%20I%20wasn't%20the%20best%20salesperson%20or%20the%20most%20well-connected%2C%20but%20I%20really%20understood%20the%20mechanics%20of%20the%20business.%20I%20used%20to%20joke%20that%20I%20had%20tried%20on%20every%20piece%20of%20inventory%20in%20the%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20grown%20up%20in%20Omaha%20and%20attended%20a%20small%20state%20college%20in%20Nebraska.%20As%20a%20buyer%2C%20I%20traveled%20to%20Switzerland%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20Las%20Vegas%20and%20learned%20more%20about%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a5295f44-ee7d-4d4e-8192-ee801efceba9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20left%20and%20came%20back%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20I%20had%20two%20kids%20with%20my%20lawyer%20husband.%20He%20was%20becoming%20a%20partner%2C%20and%20it%20got%20chaotic%20at%20home.%20I'd%20been%20working%20for%20a%20decade%20and%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20career%20break.%20We%20had%20a%20third%20child%2C%20and%20I%20stayed%20at%20home%20for%20six%20years.%20I%20maintained%20my%20connection%20with%20the%20store%2C%20sometimes%20coming%20in%20with%20the%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20after%20I%20left%2C%20Borsheims%20called%20me%20to%20ask%20me%20if%20I%20would%20consider%20coming%20back.%20I%20waited%20until%20my%20third%20child%20was%20in%20preschool%2C%20and%20then%20returned%20as%20a%20jewelry%20buyer.%20It%20was%20a%20bigger%20department%20than%20watches%2C%20and%20a%20step%20up.%20I%20loved%20my%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2274eda6b3-319b-42f4-bd24-aaabc936f5a0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20interviewed%20by%20Warren%20Buffett%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20I%20worked%20my%20way%20up%20to%20the%20executive%20team%20as%20director%20of%20merchandise.%20When%20our%20CEO%20was%20planning%20to%20leave%20for%20a%20new%20role%2C%20she%20asked%20me%20if%20I%20would%20apply%20to%20become%20CEO.%20I%20nearly%20fell%20off%20my%20chair.%20I'd%20never%20managed%20more%20than%20five%20people%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20on%20my%20radar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20asked%20to%20interview%20with%20Warren%20Buffet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20both%20from%20Omaha%2C%20which%20can%20feel%20like%20a%20small%20town.%20I%20met%20him%20briefly%20over%20the%20years%20when%20he%20came%20into%20the%20store%20and%20to%20fundraisers%20in%20Omaha%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20interview%2C%20I%20was%20so%20nervous%20my%20hands%20were%20shaking.%20We%20talked%20about%20what%20I%20thought%20of%20the%20business%20and%20its%20strengths%20and%20weaknesses%20at%20a%20high%20level.%20He%20then%20offered%20me%20a%20job%20right%20there.%20We%20didn't%20talk%20about%20salary%20or%20anything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20walked%20about%20thinking%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20even%20sure%20what%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20it%20was%20exciting.%20I'm%20still%20very%20humbled%2C%20and%20I%20pinch%20myself%20sometimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a12044c-22b9-41e6-9c66-4cf251f5e268%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20don't%20get%20nervous%20with%20Warren%20Buffett%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20I%20had%20a%20one-on-one%20with%20Warren%20Buffet%2C%20I%20was%20probably%20terrified.%20But%20he's%20so%20charming%2C%20funny%2C%20and%20informative.%20I'm%20never%20nervous%20with%20him%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20visits%20the%20store%20several%20times%20a%20year%20and%20usually%20tells%20me%20ahead%20of%20time%2C%20but%20not%20always.%20Once%2C%20I%20was%20helping%20a%20customer%20pick%20out%20some%20jewelry%2C%20and%20he%20walked%20into%20the%20store%20and%20started%20asking%20questions%20about%20inventory.%20I%20had%20to%20ask%20the%20customer%20to%20excuse%20me.%20She%20had%20no%20idea%20Warren%20Buffett%20was%20standing%20next%20to%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20a%20very%20curious%20person.%20He%20teases%20me%20about%20asking%20lots%20of%20questions%2C%20but%20I%20think%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20sitting%20with%20probably%20the%20smartest%20person%20in%20the%20world.%20Why%20wouldn't%20I%20ask%20him%20about%20everything%20from%20the%20business%20to%20our%20local%20community%20to%20sports%3F%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20talk%20about%20different%20things%20going%20on%20across%20industries%2C%20such%20as%20insurance%20or%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20greatest%20perk%20of%20my%20life%20has%20been%20having%20uninterrupted%20time%20with%20Warren%20when%20I'm%20comfortable%20enough%20to%20have%20off-the-wall%20conversations%20about%20anything%2C%20from%20soda%20to%20football.%20It's%20been%20a%20joy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20so%20supportive%20and%20kind.%20It's%20like%20talking%20to%20your%20coworker.%20I%20also%20try%20to%20be%20very%20respectful%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20contact%20him%20more%20than%20a%20couple%20of%20times%20a%20year.%20He%20is%2094.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ec427ea8-7b64-4f06-ab81-e5bcb63836cf%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe%20advised%20me%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20I'm%20good%20at%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20things%20Warren%20has%20helped%20me%20focus%20on%20is%20celebrating%20our%20successes.%20He%20hones%20in%20on%20diving%20into%20things%20you%20are%20good%20at%20to%20make%20it%20better.%20He%20reminds%20me%20to%20focus%20on%20what%20I'm%20good%20at.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20buyer%2C%20I%20was%20good%20at%20understanding%20the%20appropriate%20amount%20of%20money%20to%20spend%2C%20our%20inventory%20level%2C%20and%20how%20that%20drives%20the%20business%20for%20the%20company.%20Buying%20drives%20successful%20salespeople%20and%20happy%20customers.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20what%20I'm%20best%20at%20is%20understanding%20what%20that%20looks%20like%20at%20a%20high%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20calls%20Berkshire%20Hathaway's%20CEOs%20his%20managers.%20He%20wants%20to%20empower%20us%20to%20do%20what%20we%20think%20is%20best.%20I%20see%20him%20as%20a%20confidence%20booster.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20have%20a%20network%20of%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%20businesses%20I%20can%20call%20for%20advice.%20That's%20a%20blessing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20is%20a%20huge%20reader.%20I've%20tried%20to%20take%20that%20from%20him%20and%20read%20huge%20amounts%20of%20articles%20and%20publications.%20Knowledge%20is%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20have%20worked%20with%20a%20well-known%20business%20person%20and%20would%20like%20to%20share%20your%20story%2C%20email%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aehopkins%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eehopkins%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-work-with-warren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-borsheims-ceo-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1727689580000%2C%22visual%22%3