what-is-401k%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20403(b)%2C%20and%20457(b)%20plans.%20He%20did%20this%20to%20lower%20his%20adjusted%20gross%20income%2C%20which%20would%20lower%20his%20tax%20liability%20and%2C%20thus%2C%20his%20student%20loan%20payments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20more%20that%20you%20can%20invest%20on%20the%20front%20end%20in%20tax-beneficial%20accounts%20or%20systems%2C%20it%20will%20basically%20have%20an%20outsize%20return%20for%20you%20in%20the%20back%20end%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20used%20some%20of%20this%20excess%20money%20to%20tackle%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffeared-credit-card-debt-valuable-tool-used-right-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecredit%20card%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20he%20jumped%20to%20auditor%20positions%20that%20paid%20increasingly%20more.%20His%20debt-to-income%20ratio%20fell%20rapidly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20years%20of%20heavy%20savings%20and%20investments%2C%20he%20had%20enough%20to%20purchase%20a%20home%20for%20%24132%2C000%20in%202016%2C%20paying%20about%20%241%2C000%20each%20month%20for%20his%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20upbringing%20in%20Haiti%20%26quot%3Bgave%20me%20an%20advantage%20over%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20peers%20because%20I%20find%20that%20resourcefulness%20is%20probably%20one%20of%20those%20things%20that%20you%20need%20to%20have%2C%20especially%20when%20everybody%20thinks%20that%20things%20are%20falling%20apart%2C%26quot%3B%20Delva-Gonzalez%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20year%2C%20he%20met%20his%20now-wife%20Doreen%2C%20and%20they%20merged%20their%20accounts.%20Delva-Gonzalez%20still%20had%20debts%20to%20pay%20down%2C%20though.%20By%202017%2C%20the%20two%20of%20them%20could%20pay%20down%20debt%20to%20the%20point%20of%20having%20a%20net%20worth%20of%20zero.%20They%20employed%20various%20budgeting%20apps%20to%20keep%20expenditures%20low%20and%20pinpoint%20the%20areas%20where%20they%20overspent.%20Bot