However%2C%20the%20restoration%20of%20electricity%20is%20expected%20to%20take%20considerable%20time.%20%E2%80%9CIt's%20going%20to%20take%20weeks%20to%20fix%20it.%20We're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20start%20from%20scratch%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Russ%20Rhodes%2C%20part%20of%20a%20team%20working%20to%20replace%20a%20downed%20power%20line.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnOne%20of%20the%20town's%20most%20loved%20establishments%2C%20Roy's%20Restaurant%2C%20located%20along%20the%20Steinhatchee%20River%2C%20was%20obliterated%20by%20the%20hurricane.%20The%20restaurant%20reopened%20nine%20months%20ago%20after%20suffering%20extensive%20damage%20from%20Hurricane%20Idalia.%20%E2%80%9COur%20employees%20are%20safe.%20The%20restaurant%20didn't%20fare%20as%20well.%20But%20that's%20all%20right.%20We're%20thinking%20of%20our%20community%2C%20our%20employees%2C%20and%20everyone%20who%20is%20affected%20out%20there.%20We%20love%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20manager%20shared%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Froys.steinhatchee%2Fvideos%2F1043112834274720%2F%5C%22%3EFacebook%20Live%20message%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnDespite%20the%20overwhelming%20loss%2C%20Roy's%20owner%2C%20Linda%20Wicker%2C%20has%20vowed%20to%20rebuild%20the%2055-year-old%20restaurant.%20%E2%80%9CI%20think%20we%20need%20to%20do%20that%2C%E2%80%9D%20Wicker%20told%20the%20Palm%20Beach%20Post.%20While%20insurance%20will%20cover%20some%20of%20the%20damage%2C%20Wicker%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt's%20never%20enough%2C%E2%80%9D%20as%20she%20reflected%20on%20the%20future%20of%20her%20business%20and%20its%2030%20employees.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnSteinhatchee%20is%20just%20one%20of%20many%20coastal%20communities%20in%20Florida%20dealing%20with%20the%20severe%20impact%20of%20Hurricane%20Helene%2C%20a%20Category%204%20storm%20that%20has%20claimed%20at%20least%2045%20lives%20as%20of%20September%2028.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%20the%20nearby%20town%20of%20Perry%2C%20around%207%2C000%20residents%20are%20assessing%20